text:
Not bad! Won't say it's Taiwan taste but it's still nice in it's own ways!

Ordered the crispy chicken, curry pork cutlet rice, and braised pork rice.

Would recommend the crispy chicken!
Rice is warm not hot. Egg is cold. Pork cutlet although is piping hot but the meat is too thin, is like eating a crispy flour.
The Hot Chix Bento is quite nice. The portion size is reasonable. Service is great and the staffs are attentive.

Would like to just say that the Snackz it! Mee sua is even better than some I taste in Taiwan! The rest of the dishes are okay, but I think the real deal is the Mee Sua, where the taste is well balanced and the different toppings complete the dish for the Singaporean taste buds!
$6.90 for their combo.. choose two from s3 to s7. I got calamari and ... charcoal chicken .. carcinogen, any one?
